# Family Hub — environment template
#
# Copy to .env.local and fill in. .env.local is gitignored.
# Place at the REPO ROOT (not apps/api/). The api dev script loads it via
# --env-file=../../.env.local. In production (Railway) envs are injected
# by the platform — this file is for local dev + as a contract of what
# every service needs.
#
# This file MUST NEVER contain real secret values. Real values live in:
#   - Railway dashboard → Service → Variables (production + staging)
#   - Stripe / Supabase / Sentry dashboards (source of truth for API keys)
#   - your local .env.local (gitignored) for dev
# A shared password vault is a future follow-up — not yet ticketed; not
# needed while the project is solo.

# ─── Runtime ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NODE_ENV=development                    # development | staging | production
PORT=3001                               # api listens on this port locally
LOG_LEVEL=info                          # debug | info | warn | error (pino)

# ─── Domain ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by api for cookie domain, CORS allowlist, and tenant-slug subdomain
# resolution (ADR 0002). Locally: localhost. Staging: staging.familyhub.app.
# Production: familyhub.app.
BASE_DOMAIN=localhost
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001      # frontend reads this at build time

# ─── Postgres ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local dev: docker-compose Postgres (./scripts/dev or `pnpm dev:up`) on
# :5432 with familyhub/familyhub credentials. Railway-hosted Postgres
# injects DATABASE_URL automatically — do not paste real values here.
# Test DB runs on :5433 with fh_test/fh_test — see tests/integration/support/db.ts.
DATABASE_URL=postgres://familyhub:familyhub@localhost:5432/familyhub_dev
# DATABASE_URL_TEST=postgres://fh_test:fh_test@localhost:5433/familyhub_test

# ─── Auth (FHS-178 epic — Supabase) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Obtain from Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API.
# AUTH_SECRET is the JWT signing secret used by the api to verify tokens
# minted by Supabase. Generate with `openssl rand -base64 48` if running
# auth locally without Supabase.
# AUTH_SECRET=
# SUPABASE_URL=
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=             # server-side only, never expose to web

# ─── Stripe (FHS-68 epic — billing, Sprint 4) ──────────────────────────────
# Obtain from Stripe dashboard → Developers → API keys (test mode for dev).
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=                     # sk_test_… (dev) / sk_live_… (prod)
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=                 # whsec_… from Stripe CLI or dashboard
# STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=                # pk_test_… exposed to web

# ─── Sentry (FHS-166 — observability) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Obtain from Sentry dashboard → Project Settings → Client Keys (DSN).
# Originally scoped as a single SENTRY_DSN; split per Sentry project
# (api = Node runtime, web = browser runtime) so client crashes and
# server errors are filed separately. Either var alone satisfies the
# "Sentry DSN" contract for its surface.
# SENTRY_DSN_API=
# SENTRY_DSN_WEB=

# ─── Jira ↔ GitHub automation (used by /tmp/*.py scripts, not the api) ─────
# Obtain Jira API token from https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens.
# EMAIL=you@example.com
# JIRA_API_TOKEN=
# URL=https://qualicion2.atlassian.net/

# ─── Railway (FHS-156 — Railway MCP server in .mcp.json) ───────────────────
# Mint at https://railway.com/account/tokens (Account Tokens, not Project).
# .mcp.json is gitignored; each contributor adds their own MCP via:
#   claude mcp add railway --scope local --env RAILWAY_API_TOKEN=$RAILWAY_API_TOKEN \
#       -- npx -y @jasontanswe/railway-mcp
# RAILWAY_API_TOKEN=
